content: Pretty nice, i like it.

Took me about 10 mins to set up since I didn't know how to, I got a new tablet for Christmas. Anyways, if anyone else is having problems: add widget to homescreen (press + at the top was what I had to do) and scroll down until you see 'subwoofer'. Drag that to your homescreen. Go to settings, display, wallpaper, live wallpaper and choose the subwoofer one. Go to your homescreen, play some music through any app, and turn the volume up so its loud. The subwoofer in the background will then move to the bass notes in the music. To get a different angle use the widget, tap on a view angle. Enjoy!  Shame the app didnt tell me how to about this, I was a little worried for a while. Anyways, its a neat little app. Worth 99p :) and by the way, Daniel munson's review is good, his ideas are pretty cool! Thanks for the great app!
